<title>USA: Adobe stock falls on disappointing earnings.</title>
<headline>Adobe stock falls on disappointing earnings.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>The stock of Adobe Systems Inc. fell Thursday, one day after the software maker reported lower than expected earnings.</p>
<p>Adobe was off $4.50 at $35.75 in active trading of more than 4.3 million shares on the Nasdaq market.</p>
<p>Late Wednesday, the San Jose, Calif.-based company said it earned $40.1 million, or 54 cents a share, on revenues of $228.3 million in its fiscal second quarter ended May 30 vs. year-ago earnings of $22.0 million, or 29 cents a share, on revenues of $204.3 million.</p>
<p>The per share earnings were 5 cents below Wall Street's expectations, analysts said.</p>
